This strategy is inspired by publicly discussed prop firm methodologies and ICT (Inner Circle Trader) concepts focused on liquidity, market structure shifts, and price imbalances.

It is not affiliated with, endorsed by, or connected to Zamco Capital Ltd, ICT, or Michael Huddleston.
This script is provided strictly for educational and research purposes.

OVERVIEW
This rule-based strategy implements core ICT concepts using standard OHLC data available on TradingView.

The model focuses on:
Liquidity sweeps of recent swing highs/lows
Market Structure Shift (MSS) confirmation
Fair Value Gap (FVG) imbalance zones
Higher Timeframe (HTF) EMA 50/200 directional bias

The objective is to participate in directional moves after liquidity has been taken and short-term structure confirms displacement.

This is not predictive trading. It is reactive to confirmed structural shifts.

CORE LOGIC
1. HTF Bias Filter
EMA 50 and EMA 200 on a configurable higher timeframe define macro direction.
Only trades aligned with HTF direction are considered.

2. Liquidity Sweep Detection
Price must first take a prior swing high or low before any setup becomes valid.

3. Market Structure Shift (MSS)
After the sweep, a break of opposing structure confirms potential shift in order flow.

4. Execution Rules
Entry: Market order on MSS confirmation bar
Stop Loss: Beyond swept liquidity level
Take Profit: Fixed risk-to-reward (default 3R)
One position at a time (no pyramiding)

FEATURES
Liquidity sweep markers with level visualization
Market structure shift lines with price labels
Fair Value Gap zones with optional equilibrium midline
Higher timeframe EMA ribbon
Session background shading (London & New York)
Compact dashboard (bias, session, structure state, R:R)
Alert() support for automation

BACKTEST INFORMATION
Backtests depend heavily on:
Instrument
Timeframe
Spread and commission
Slippage
Market regime
Risk settings

Results will vary significantly across symbols and periods.
Users should configure realistic trading costs in Strategy Properties before evaluating performance.

The sample backtest shown in the chart is for demonstration purposes only and represents a limited historical window.

RECOMMENDED SETTINGS

Entry Timeframes:
5-minute
15-minute

Suggested HTF Bias:
Use 4H HTF when trading 5m or 15m charts
Use Daily HTF when trading 1H charts

Common Instruments:
XAUUSD
NAS100
GER40
BTCUSD
ETHUSD

Default Risk-to-Reward: 3.0

IMPORTANT CLARIFICATIONS
This script approximates ICT concepts using candle data only.
It does not use real bid/ask order flow or institutional execution data.

Performance is highly sensitive to configuration and market conditions.
Past performance does not guarantee future results.

AUTOMATION
TradingView alerts can be connected to supported brokers using third-party automation services.
Automation configuration is optional and not required to use this script.

EDUCATIONAL DISCLAIMER
This strategy is provided for educational and research purposes only.
It is not financial advice.

Users are responsible for their own risk management, testing, and trading decisions.
Forward-testing on a demo or simulated account is strongly recommended before considering live execution.


